{
  "texts": [
    "A number of experiments are performed at different values of parameter K which varies from 10 to 80 with an increment of 10 and the parameter α is set to its optimal value for our proposed approach and semantically enhanced-CF approach proposed by Mobasher et al. [16] as illustrated in the second previous experiment.",
    "Figure 4 shows the MAE improvement of the proposed approach against other competing approaches according to the K parameter.",
    "It shows that the proposed approach achieves substantially better results in terms of prediction accuracy compared to the other competing approaches.",
    "As Fig. 4 shows, when the size of the K parameter is higher than 60, the MAE value tends to gradually increase for all compared approaches.",
    "The underlying rationale can be attributed to the diminished capacity for accurate predictions by all approaches as the neighborhood size for each item expanded, intensifying the differences between items."
  ]
}